  "prompt": "How can I add a floating chart (like freezing top row) in Excel 2013?",
  "response": "In Excel 2013, you can create a floating chart that remains visible as you scroll through your worksheet by using a camera tool or by leveraging the chart's floating properties. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n### Method 1: Create a Floating Chart Using the Camera Tool\n1. **Create Your Chart:**\n   - Select the data range you want to chart.\n   - Go to the **Insert** tab and choose the type of chart you want to create.\n\n2. **Copy the Chart as a Picture:**\n   - Select the chart.\n   - Right-click and choose **Copy**, or press `Ctrl + C`.\n   - Go to the **Home** tab, click on the **Paste** dropdown, and select **Picture**.\n\n3. **Anchor the Picture to a Cell:**\n   - Cut the picture (`Ctrl + X`).\n   - Select a cell where you want the chart to float, then paste the picture (`Ctrl + V`).\n   - The picture will now float above the cells and remain visible as you scroll.\n\n### Method 2: Make the Chart Float Using the Freeze Panes Option\n1. **Create Your Chart:**\n   - Select the data range you want to chart.\n   - Go to the **Insert** tab and choose the type of chart you want to create.\n\n2. **Move the Chart to a New Sheet:**\n   - Right-click on the chart and select **Move Chart**.\n   - Choose **New Sheet** and click **OK**.\n   - The chart will now be on its own sheet, and you can switch between sheets as needed.\n\n3. **Freeze Panes in the Original Sheet:**\n   - Go back to the sheet with your data.\n   - Select the row or column you want to freeze (e.g., the top row).\n   - Go to the **View** tab and click **Freeze Panes**.\n   - Choose **Freeze Top Row** to keep the top row visible as you scroll.\n\n### Method 3: Move the Chart to a Corner and Adjust Zoom\n1. **Create Your Chart:**\n   - Select the data range you want to chart.\n   - Go to the **Insert** tab and choose the type of chart you want to create.\n\n2. **Move the Chart to a Corner:**\n   - Drag the chart to a corner of the worksheet where it won\u2019t interfere with your data.\n\n3. **Adjust Zoom:**\n   - Use the zoom slider in the bottom-right corner of Excel to zoom out, so you can see both the chart and the data as you scroll.\n\nThese methods will help you keep your chart visible while working with large datasets in Excel 2013.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
